id: pm-wcaa
title: MCP pm_files discover/apply/discoveryNote params are declared but ignored by the files action handler
description: "The pm_files tool schema (PM_TOOL_ACTION_SCHEMA_CONTRACTS.files in src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts) declares optional discover, apply, and discoveryNote parameters, but runAction's 'files' case in src/mcp/server.ts passes options straight to runFiles, which reads none of them - pm_files {discover:true} silently returns the plain link listing instead of running discovery. Discovery is only reachable via pm_run action 'files-discover' (note param there). Fix options: route case 'files' to runFilesDiscover when options.discover===true (mapping discoveryNote->note, honoring apply/appendStable), or drop the three params from the files schema contract and document pm_run files-discover as the only path. Found 2026-06-12 while wiring pm-pfnx (--note/addNote)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,dogfood,mcp
created_at: "2026-06-11T22:13:41.473Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-11T22:42:05.186Z"
author: cli-fixes-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: implemented
expected_result: MCP pm_files discover/apply/discoveryNote parameters perform file discovery and apply discovered links through the narrow MCP tool.
actual_result: "pm_files discover=true now routes to runFilesDiscover, maps discoveryNote to note, preserves normal runFiles behavior, and passes MCP integration plus temp-project smoke."
